node.text:
She’s a little sass and a lot of BADASS!

Your power lies not on the surface, but deep within you. Using your power of decision gives you the capacity to get past any excuse to change any and every part of your life in an instant. 

Willpower is not genetic. It requires the will to resist and the power of a resolved mind. We’ve all heard the old saying “where there’s a will there’s a way” and it’s true! You must decide exactly what you want to accomplish and then resolve to pay the price to get it. We all have to pay our dues. 

Resolve to be a master of change rather than a victim of change. 

Let me help you turn your pain into power and then turn that POWER into GROWTH!

I have spots left for October in my FULL custom 8 week coaching programs. (check out my client reel to see some amazing transformations!) Email me for more info on this!  (caitlinr.fit@gmail.com) Full Coaching includes:

✅Weekly Checkins
🍎Custom Diet and Recipes
🍑Booty Workouts
📝Customized training programs
📲Access to my cell for any questions you have along the way
 ➕and more!

I also now offer IN PERSON TRAINING! All programs will come with a fully customized diet as well 🙌🔥 let me help you reach your goals!! Let’s GO!

🎥 @_johnhassan 
🦵pink pants @dtinas_ leopard print @ethos_co 
💊 fat burner and pre workout @steelsupplements code CAITLIN

Photo dump 😍 

Tucson, thanks for being so green this weekend. I’ve come to realize there are only two climates in AZ. Hot. And slightly less hot. 🤪

Slow down and enjoy life. It's not only the scenery you miss by going to fast - you also miss the sense of where you are going and why. Spend more time with people that slow you down. That ground you and keep you present. ❤️

node.text:
What do you see when you look in the mirror? Are you proud of the person looking back at you? Do you know that person deeply and intimately or do you see a stranger gazing back at you? 

I haven’t always loved the girl looking back at me. And I haven’t always been the strong, independent, successful and confident woman I am today. I’ve been anxious, I’ve been broken, I’ve been hurt, weak etc. It’s taken me years of hard intentional work on personal development, on my mental state, and my emotional intelligence to get to where I am now. I learned to be with myself rather than avoiding myself with limiting habits; I started to be aware of my feelings more, rather than numb them. 

My confidence comes from WHO I am on the inside, not my outer shell. It comes from knowing myself deeply and moving in alignment with it. It comes from knowing that I am capable of absolutely anything I set my mind to and my options are limitless. And it was built by honoring the commitments I have made to myself and by following through on the actions that are required to be the woman I want and know I can be.

I no longer deal with anxiety or stress and I do not let my emotions run me. I never operate in the “red” . I am excellent at regulating my emotions and remaining calm and just finding solutions to problems instead of stressing for no reason. I’ve spent a lot of time becoming emotionally intelligent and I don’t ever let myself get off balance. When I feel a slide or a slight pull towards feeling anxious I sit down with myself and dive deep on why I’m feeling the way I’m feeling and then honor those emotions for a moment and then find a solution to give myself what I need to move past it. This is only possible because of my intimate knowledge of myself.
